Emoji have already taken over the web and now they're gunning for real world too.

Developers have created a keyboard cover that turns every key of the board into one of the small, iconic pictures.

Once installed, the Caps Lock key lets users switch between regular and emoji keys meaning people can easily add images to Facebook posts, tweets and even official documents.

