The team has set up a Kickstarter campaign to fund production of at least 1,000 covers, but hopes to be able to mass produce them by the end of the year. 

At the time of writing it has raised more than $3,570 (£2,400)  of its $20,000 (£13,500) target. 

Each of the covers are made of silicone and act like standard covers to block out dust, dirt and liquid.

They come in two sizes -  one for standard Macs, which includes the 13-inch and 15-inch MacBook Pro, the MacBook Air 13 and the Apple Wireless Mac keyboard, and one for the 11-inch MacBook Air. 

